=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Alternatives to the snare whip</span><hr size=1> After following this forum for as long as I have you tend to see these topics come and go.  It's a real shame ezboard has such an awful search function and/or we can't develop a way to archive some of the more common questions as I hate to post a question I know was on here not more than six months ago.<br>
<br>
I have the good old fashioned fb/ silken whip of ensnaring combo that I have been using to MT for most any situation and I'm starting to wonder if there is another rather inexpensive (1k'ish)weapon out there that I can rep the snare whip with?  The reason I say inexpensive is because I am one drop away from my epic and a) dont have the plat to spend &amp; b) don't want to waste money because I will be going fb/epic for mt situations.<br>
<br>
I caught on the bbot trend and picked one up in the bazaar for a meager sum and have been testing it out.  I haven't had a chance to really use it enough to make a final call but I have to wonder if there are any more of these &quot;gems&quot; out there to give a try? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=healsdata>HealsData</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/02 9:31:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4706.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re:</span><hr size=1> Up until this week, I was using a Frostbringer and a snare whip as well. I was *insulted* by a ranger who I was grouped with that sent me a tell and said &quot;Your taunt skill is maxxed out, isn't it?&quot;<br>
<br>
